#1. What are Daemons in Linux?
A daemon is a program that runs in the background without direct user interaction and waits to perform specific tasks whenever needed.

* Why are Daemons Needed?
Imagine a computer where every service had to be started manually each time:
Printing wouldn't work automatically.
Network connections wouldn't be managed automatically.
Web servers wouldn't respond to requests continuously.

Daemons solve this problem by running in the background and handling these services automatically.
 *Common Linux Daemons
__________________________________________
| Daemon    | Purpose                    |
| --------- | -------------------------- |
| `lpd`     | Print spooling service     |
| `sshd`    | Handles SSH remote logins  |
| `cron`    | Runs scheduled tasks       |
| `systemd` | System and service manager |
| `httpd`   | Web server daemon          |
| `named`   | DNS server daemon          |
|________________________________________|

*Characteristics of Daemons
* Run in Background

They do not require user interaction.

* Start Automatically

Many daemons start during system boot.

* Provide Services

They wait for requests and respond when needed.

* Long-Lived Processes

They may run for days, weeks, or months until the system shuts down.

#2. Shutdown vs Sleep vs Hibernate
__________________________________________________________
| Feature            | Sleep     | Hibernate   | Shutdown |
| ------------------ | --------- | ----------- | -------- |
| Power Consumption  | Low       | Almost Zero | Zero     |
| RAM Active         | Yes       | No          | No       |
| Current Work Saved | Yes       | Yes         | No       |
| Resume Speed       | Very Fast | Medium      | Slowest  |
| Battery Required   | Yes       | No          | No       |
|_________________________________________________________|
*Easy Rule
Short break → Sleep 😴
Long break but work save rakhna → Hibernate 🐻
Kaam khatam → Shutdown 🔴
#3. SSD vs HDD
____________________________________________________________________
| Feature           | SSD                | HDD                     |
| ----------------- | ------------------ | ----------------------- |
| Technology        | Flash Memory Chips | Spinning Magnetic Disks |
| Speed             | Very Fast          | Slower                  |
| Noise             | Silent             | Mechanical Sound        |
| Power Consumption | Less               | More                    |
| Durability        | Better             | Less                    |
| Moving Parts      | No                 | Yes                     |
| Boot Time         | 5-20 sec           | 30-90 sec               |
| Price per GB      | Higher             | Lower                   |
|__________________________________________________________________|
